// App Name Visit Chattanooga
// Attractions List Items Chattanooga Zoo 301 N. Holtzclaw Ave, Chattanooga, TN 37404 Lions, tigers, and jaguars?! You can see them all at the Chattanooga Zoo at Warner Park. It\'s a 13-acre zoological park located in Warner Park in Chattanooga, Tennessee.
Tennessee Aquarium One Broad Street, Chattanooga, TN 37402 The Tennessee Aquarium opened in 1992 on the banks of the Tennessee River in downtown Chattanooga. It is home to more than 12,000 and is a definite MUST SEE while your in town.
Rock City 1400 Patten Rd., Lookout Mountain, GA 30750 Rock City is a marvel of nature featuring ancient rock formations, gardens with over 400 native plant species, and breathtaking "See 7 States" panoramic views.
Lake Winnepesaukah 1730 Lakeview Dr., Rossville, GA 30741 Lake Winnepesaukah, commonly known as Lake Winnie, is an amusement park located in Rossville, Georgia, just south of Chattanooga, Tennessee. It\'s a great spot to have fun with family and friend while satisfying your inner thrill-seeker.
// Events List Items Riverbend Festival 200 Riverfront Parkway, Chattanooga, TN 37402 The Riverbend Festival is an 8 day music festival that occurs every July, and it is jam packed with fun and great artists.
Movies in Coolidge Park 150 River Street, Chattanooga, TN 37405 Grab your lawn chairs, blankets, snacks and head to Coolidge Park to enjoy some movies under the stars.
Chattanooga Market 1826 Reggie White Boulevard, Chattanooga, TN 37408 Chattanooga Market features over 50 farms bringing a variety of produce, meats and cheeses to the market each week.
// Food List Items Urban Stack 12 W 13th St, Chattanooga, TN 37402 Urban Stack is a great place to grab a burger and a drink with friends.
Public House Chattanooga 1110 Market St, Chattanooga, TN 37402 Public House Chattanooga serves up local produce southern-style.
Sluggo\'s North Vegetarian Cafe 501 Cherokee Blvd., Chattanooga, TN 37405 Sluggo\'s is an awesome restaurant that serves up delicious vegetarian meals.
/ History List Items Chattanooga Choo Choo 1400 Market Street, Chattanooga, TN 37402 The Chattanooga Choo Choo is much more than a song! This historic train terminal was saved from demolition in 1973 and today it\'s a popular hotel downtown, attracting visitors from all over.
Chattanooga Civil War Museum 3914 Street Elmo Avenue, Chattanooga, TN 37409 The civil war museum is the spot for history buffs interested in learning more about the cities ties to the civil war.
Chickamauga Dam 4795 Amnicola Highway, Chattanooga, TN 37402 The Chickamauga Dam is a hydroelectric dam located on the Tennessee River.
